This paper deals with the problem of processing trajectory datasets, which is a common task in data management. The use of MapReduce programming model suggests that the paper belongs to the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The focus on trajectory data management and the use of indexing schemes suggest that the paper also belongs to the category of Databases (cs.DB) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). The use of real-world datasets and the experimental study suggest that the paper also belongs to the category of Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science (cs.CE) and Machine Learning (cs.LG).
